==English==

===Noun===
''[[Mythical]]'' A [[human]] [[possessed]] by a [[wolf]] [[spirit]], [[cover]]ed with [[fur]] and [[unable]] to [[control]] his [[savage]] [[bloodlust]].  Usually is a [[normal]] human [[except]] for the [[night]]s around the [[full moon]].

====Etymology====
[[Old English]] ''werewulf'': ''were'' man + ''wulf'' wolf

====Historical Note====
The myth probably originates with the disease [[w:Lupus Erythematosus|lupus erythematosus]] , which causes afflicted people to grow extra hair and avoid sunlight.  "Lupus" is [[Latin]] for "wolf".  The [[vampire]] myth may have the same origin.

